This paper is primarily focused on the Internet of Things (IoT) and energy harvesting, which falls under the category of networked and distributed systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses contract theory and incentive mechanisms, which are related to game theory (cs.GT) and information theory (cs.IT). The optimization of the contract and the analysis of the feasibility of the proposed mechanism involve mathematical modeling and control theory, which are related to systems and control (cs.SY) and cybernetics (cs.CY).
